Heather



From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
purplespacefriend
Sent: Wednesday, April 01, 2009 9:44 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: OVILUS



I made a similar device using the same voice chip, and no dictionary. I used
the random voltage generator from the boxes to make a random number
gnerator, and that was all I used to access the Speakjet. I had the thing at
the Stanley last year, and after a talk a woman came up to the table and
asked &quot;do they only speak for you?&quot; the RoboBox, as I called it, imediately
repeated &quot;for you&quot;, followed a few seconds later by &quot;loves to cook&quot;. The
woman was a cook. While it would sound like R2D2 on LSD, it often put out
meaningful phrases. 

Hopefully I didn&#39;t offend everyone, but I am pretty biased when it comes to
the so called paranormal, and ghost hunting. The focus on the fear and
negativity really gets to me. 

Frank-S

